# File: SeatValue.py
# Description: There are three seating categories at a stadium. Class A seats cost $20, Class B seats cost $15, and Class C seats cost $10. Write a program that asks how many tickets for each class of seats were sold, then displays the amount of income generated from ticket sales.
# Assignment Name and Number: Stadium Seating, 7
#
# Name: Noah Postelle
# GitHub: noahpostelle
#
# On my honor, Noah Postelle, this programming assignment is my own work
# and I have not provided this code to any other student.





SeatA = float(input("How many tickets sold in Class A: "))
SeatB = float(input("How many tickets sold in Class B: "))
SeatC = float(input("How many tickets sold in Class C: "))

Amoney = 20
Bmoney = 15
Cmoney = 10

Avalue = Amoney * SeatA
Bvalue = Bmoney * SeatB
Cvalue = Cmoney * SeatC

print("The total for class a was: $",Avalue)
print("The total for class b was: $",Bvalue)
print("The total for class c was: $",Cvalue)
